But you're bunch of cowboys.

1378
01:20:44.799 --> 01:20:47.385
<i>So while the consciousness
of the planet is unified</i>

1379
01:20:47.468 --> 01:20:49.971
<i>focused on the NASA mission
taking place right now</i>

1380
01:20:50.054 --> 01:20:51.889
<i>in the vast ocean of space.</i>

1381
01:20:51.973 --> 01:20:53.975
<i>we're now in the final hours
of the mission</i>

1382
01:20:54.058 --> 01:20:57.478
<i>as the</i> Freedom <i>and</i> Independence
<i>prepare to slingshot around the moon.</i>

1383
01:21:06.112 --> 01:21:07.864
Morning. guys.

1384
01:21:07.947 --> 01:21:11.451
It's time to suit up. I guess.
We got a big day.

1385
01:21:11.951 --> 01:21:15.621
- Eighteen seconds to radio interrupt.
- Booster sequence confirmed.

1386
01:21:15.705 --> 01:21:18.875
<i>This is Houston.
Roger that.</i> Freedom. <i>We copy.</i>

1387
01:21:18.958 --> 01:21:20.752
Shuttles are ready
for the burn around the moon.

1388
01:21:20.835 --> 01:21:23.337
Radio contact terminated. We're out.

1389
01:21:24.672 --> 01:21:28.926
Nine and a half Gs for 11 minutes.
I'd start praying about right now.

1390
01:21:34.265 --> 01:21:36.809
So this is the part where we're
supposed to just hold on real tight

1391
01:21:36.893 --> 01:21:38.352
and hope we don't die.

1392
01:21:38.436 --> 01:21:42.190
- Stand by for lunar roll.
- High inclination. Lunar orbit.

1393
01:21:44.525 --> 01:21:47.528
You boys got those wills
filled out correctly?

1394
01:22:03.002 --> 01:22:04.921
All right. men.
this is what we trained for.

1395
01:22:05.004 --> 01:22:06.339
Now just suck it up!

1396
01:22:06.422 --> 01:22:11.761
On the mark. Five. four. three. two. one.

1397
01:22:22.188 --> 01:22:25.108
- Is this supposed to be like this?
- Don't worry. This is normal.

1398
01:22:25.191 --> 01:22:28.653
- How would you know?
- 14.000 miles an hour.

1399
01:22:28.736 --> 01:22:31.405
- Four Gs.
- How long does this last?

1400
01:22:31.489 --> 01:22:32.615
Six Gs.

1401
01:22:35.493 --> 01:22:36.619
15.000.

1402
01:22:36.702 --> 01:22:38.746
- Really heavy. man!
- This isn't normal.

1403
01:22:38.830 --> 01:22:40.081
What do you mean.
"This isn't normal"?

1404
01:22:40.164 --> 01:22:41.833
This is way worse!

1405
01:22:41.916 --> 01:22:45.294
- Eight Gs. Hang tight!
- I'm not gonna make it!

1406
01:22:45.378 --> 01:22:48.172
We're gonna die!

1407
01:22:48.256 --> 01:22:50.550
Twelve minutes.
Flight. we still got nothing here.

1408
01:22:52.260 --> 01:22:55.012
This is too fast!

1409
01:22:58.766 --> 01:22:59.976
Ten Gs!

1410
01:23:12.738 --> 01:23:16.742
We're maxed at 22.500!

1411
01:23:26.627 --> 01:23:30.089
<i>We have acquisition of signal
from</i> Independence <i>and</i> Freedom.

1412
01:23:30.173 --> 01:23:33.217
We're in. guys.
All right. Welcome back. team.

1413
01:23:33.301 --> 01:23:35.595
We have visual of the target. Houston.

1414
01:23:44.979 --> 01:23:46.439
You see that?

1415
01:23:51.277 --> 01:23:52.486
Wow.

1416
01:23:55.615 --> 01:23:57.116
Come in. <i>independence.</i>

1417
01:23:57.200 --> 01:23:59.994
<i>Houston. you gotta see this
to believe it.</i>

1418
01:24:02.121 --> 01:24:03.789
Okay. team. let's take them in.

1419
01:24:03.873 --> 01:24:05.583
Okay. Quincy.
how much tail debris do we have?

1420
01:24:05.666 --> 01:24:07.752
Freedom. <i>turn on your FOD radar.</i>

1421
01:24:07.835 --> 01:24:09.337
FOD radar on.

1422
01:24:11.672 --> 01:24:13.925
Everybody. hang on.
This could get a little rough.

1423
01:24:14.008 --> 01:24:15.343
Engaging evasive radar.

1424
01:24:23.309 --> 01:24:24.518
Hold on!

1425
01:24:36.072 --> 01:24:37.990
Goddamn! We got debris!

1426
01:24:39.909 --> 01:24:41.827
<i>We're dumping auxiliary boosters.</i>

1427
01:24:55.675 --> 01:24:58.344
<i>-Houston. do you read me?
- We got debris!</i>

1428
01:25:00.972 --> 01:25:02.723
- We're going in!
- We're coming in hot!

1429
01:25:07.270 --> 01:25:08.854
Independence. <i>try to maintain
your present heading.</i>

1430
01:25:08.938 --> 01:25:10.106
<i>You've got a target L.Z.</i>

1431
01:25:10.189 --> 01:25:12.316
There's too much debris!
We gotta peel off!

1432
01:25:12.400 --> 01:25:13.442
Negative!

1433
01:25:16.696 --> 01:25:17.697
We're hit!

1434
01:25:20.992 --> 01:25:22.076
Mayday. mayday!

1435
01:25:22.159 --> 01:25:23.911
I've lost main thrusters.
Get them back up!

1436
01:25:23.995 --> 01:25:26.289
Mayday. Houston. mayday!
We've lost R.C.S. thrusters!

1437
01:25:26.372 --> 01:25:28.165
<i>Mayday.</i> Freedom. <i>mayday!</i>

1438
01:25:28.249 --> 01:25:30.334
We are out of control!
We are going down!

1439
01:25:30.418 --> 01:25:32.878
Do you read me?
<i>Freedom. we</i> are going down!

1440
01:25:46.225 --> 01:25:47.393
We're gonna hit!

1441
01:25:57.570 --> 01:26:01.907
Everybody. go to your own life support!
Lock yourself in the cargo bay!

1442
01:26:03.951 --> 01:26:05.077
We are going down!

1443
01:26:05.411 --> 01:26:09.040
Houston! Houston. we are going down!
We have lost control!

1444
01:26:09.123 --> 01:26:10.791
I can't get it on!

1445
01:26:13.044 --> 01:26:16.464
- Good luck. <i>Freedom.</i>
- Oh. my God. this is it.

1446
01:26:25.014 --> 01:26:27.099
No! No!

1447
01:26:33.064 --> 01:26:36.192
Pull it! Pull it! Go!

1448
01:27:07.139 --> 01:27:10.643
Sharp. what the hell is that?
Is that the <i>independence?</i>

1449
01:27:15.314 --> 01:27:17.525
<i>Houston.</i> Independence
<i>is a dead stick.</i>

1450
01:27:17.608 --> 01:27:18.776
<i>They're not gonna make it.</i>

1451
01:27:31.664 --> 01:27:33.833
<i>Houston.</i> Independence
<i>has gone down.</i>

1452
01:27:46.345 --> 01:27:48.597
When I touch this baby down.
full reverse thrust.

1453
01:27:48.681 --> 01:27:51.517
- Fires on your right. Sharp!
- Reversing the thrusters!

1454
01:27:52.893 --> 01:27:54.812
Hang tight! Hang tight!

1455
01:27:55.729 --> 01:27:57.773
Houston. we overshot our landing field.

1456
01:27:57.857 --> 01:28:01.235
- We overshot our landing field.
- Oh. no!

1457
01:28:21.380 --> 01:28:22.465
God!

1458
01:28:38.898 --> 01:28:42.693
Initiate system light system check.
Make sure we can still get off this rock.

1459
01:28:42.776 --> 01:28:45.279
Our electrical system is screwed.
I'm going to back-up.

1460
01:28:45.362 --> 01:28:47.323
Fuel seals check. Engine seals check.

1461
01:28:47.406 --> 01:28:49.700
- Pressure seals check.
- God.

1462
01:28:53.370 --> 01:28:56.499
- Anyone hurt?
- God.

1463
01:28:56.582 --> 01:29:02.171
Where's... Where's the other shuttle?
What happened to the other shuttle?

1464
01:29:02.254 --> 01:29:05.508
- <i>Independence</i> is off the grid.
- "Off the grid"?

1465
01:29:05.591 --> 01:29:09.094
What are you. a freaking cyborg?
What does that mean?

1466
01:29:09.178 --> 01:29:12.598
Hey. you saw it yourself. right?
They're gone.

1467
01:29:14.642 --> 01:29:16.685
Come in. <i>Freedom.</i>
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1468
01:29:16.769 --> 01:29:18.229
<i>Freedom.</i> come in.

1469
01:29:18.312 --> 01:29:21.065
This is CAPCOM Houston.
Come in. <i>Freedom.</i>

1470
01:29:21.941 --> 01:29:22.983
God!

1471
01:29:23.067 --> 01:29:26.111
Let's just ask God
to take care of our friends.

1472
01:29:27.696 --> 01:29:29.615
May they rest in peace.

1473
01:29:31.033 --> 01:29:32.117
Amen.

1474
01:29:40.167 --> 01:29:41.919
We got eight hours.

1475
01:29:43.045 --> 01:29:45.589
Let's get this job done and go home.

1476
01:29:46.549 --> 01:29:49.510
Nothing. Come on. Watts.
Sharp. somebody.

1477
01:29:50.636 --> 01:29:52.513
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1478
01:29:53.889 --> 01:29:57.601
Come in. <i>Freedom. Freedom.</i> come in.
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1479
01:29:59.645 --> 01:30:01.772
- Maybe you shouldn't be here.
- Come in. <i>Freedom.</i>

1480
01:30:01.855 --> 01:30:04.191
I don't have anywhere else to go.

1481
01:30:04.275 --> 01:30:06.068
<i>Freedom.</i> come in.
This is CAPCOM Houston.

1482
01:30:08.320 --> 01:30:10.948
All right. let's get the tools unpacked
and fire up the Armadillo.

1483
01:30:11.031 --> 01:30:13.325
We're not getting a damn thing
on the inertial nav system.

1484
01:30:13.409 --> 01:30:15.828
- I know where we are.
- Please step away.

1485
01:30:15.911 --> 01:30:17.288
Radio signal's dead.

1486
01:30:17.371 --> 01:30:19.081
I'm flipping the backup generator.

1487
01:30:19.164 --> 01:30:21.584
Radio signal's gonna be cut in half
till we get main power back.

1488
01:30:21.667 --> 01:30:27.172
We're in segment 202. lateral grid 9.
site 15H-32. give or take a few yards.

1489
01:30:27.256 --> 01:30:30.926
Captain America here
blew the landing by 26 miles.

1490
01:30:31.010 --> 01:30:34.763
- How the hell do you know that?
- Because I'm a genius.

1491
01:30:34.847 --> 01:30:36.223
The gauges will not read.

1492
01:30:36.307 --> 01:30:38.601
They're all peaked. like we're plugged
into some magnetic field.

1493
01:30:38.684 --> 01:30:40.561
Well. who on this spaceship
wants to know why?

1494
01:30:40.644 --> 01:30:42.980
- By all means.
- The reason we were shooting for grid 8

1495
01:30:43.063 --> 01:30:44.565
was because
thermographics indicated

1496
01:30:44.648 --> 01:30:47.359
that grid 9 was compressed iron ferrite.

1497
01:30:48.902 --> 01:30:52.114
Which means you landed us
on a goddamn iron plate.

1498
01:30:54.908 --> 01:30:55.951
All right. Well. you heard the man.

1499
01:30:56.035 --> 01:30:58.203
Let's wheel out the remote satellite link.
We need that radio.

1500
01:30:58.287 --> 01:31:01.457
God. please tell me
we still got one of them.

1501
01:31:02.875 --> 01:31:05.044
Independence <i>has flat-lined.</i>

1502
01:31:49.672 --> 01:31:51.924
Oscar! Oscar!

1503
01:31:54.259 --> 01:31:56.428
God!

1504
01:31:59.515 --> 01:32:06.063
Hello! Anyone! Is anyone else alive?
Somebody help me!

1505
01:32:07.815 --> 01:32:09.024
A.J.!

1506
01:32:10.609 --> 01:32:13.362
- Where are you?
- I'm here.

1507
01:32:18.283 --> 01:32:22.788
Lev. there's no one else.
There's no one else.

1508
01:32:22.871 --> 01:32:26.792
- I know.
- Oh. man.

1509
01:32:26.875 --> 01:32:29.878
- Bear. where are you?
- A.J.! A.J.!

1510
01:32:31.630 --> 01:32:34.675
- I'm in the shuttle. man.
- Bear.

1511
01:32:34.758 --> 01:32:36.802
Are you all right?

1512
01:32:36.885 --> 01:32:39.221
I'm so glad to see you. man.

1513
01:32:39.304 --> 01:32:42.474
I never thought I'd be so happy
to see your ugly face.

1514
01:32:42.808 --> 01:32:44.184
Houston. do you read?

1515
01:32:44.268 --> 01:32:46.437
- This is <i>Freedom.
- Check your thrusters.</i>

1516
01:32:46.520 --> 01:32:49.648
- <i>Houston. do you copy?</i>
- Is everyone good to go?

1517
01:33:00.909 --> 01:33:01.994
Wow.

1518
01:33:12.755 --> 01:33:15.007
Down here! In the valley!

1519
01:33:16.216 --> 01:33:19.094
This place is like
Dr Seuss' worst nightmare.

1520
01:33:19.178 --> 01:33:23.932
Let's get the remote satellite.
We'll get better reception up there.

1521
01:33:24.016 --> 01:33:25.601
Bring Max down.

1522
01:33:25.684 --> 01:33:28.854
Watch yourself through here. Max.
There's a couple big fissures.

1523
01:33:28.937 --> 01:33:31.648
To the left! Bring it to the left!

1524
01:33:37.571 --> 01:33:38.947
Rockhound. you come on down here

1525
01:33:39.031 --> 01:33:40.991
and take some readings
down in the flat spot.

1526
01:33:43.994 --> 01:33:45.162
Iron ferrite.

1527
01:33:48.665 --> 01:33:50.250
I have fire.

1528
01:33:50.334 --> 01:33:53.128
Watts. I'm coming back. Stand by.

1529
01:33:53.212 --> 01:33:57.049
- Mostly iron. Rockhound.
- God. I hate knowing everything.

1530
01:33:57.341 --> 01:33:59.968
We couldn't have picked
a worse spot to drill.

1531
01:34:00.052 --> 01:34:04.181
Well. I can pretty much guarantee
it's not gonna be thicker than 50 feet.

1532
01:34:04.264 --> 01:34:07.226
- How do you figure that?
- 'Cause if it is. we're screwed.

1533
01:34:09.436 --> 01:34:12.105
- Max. you good?
- Yeah. Just making hole.

1534
01:34:12.189 --> 01:34:15.192
- Turn it around.
- Frigging outer space.

1535
01:34:18.278 --> 01:34:19.613
It's good.

1536
01:34:26.745 --> 01:34:30.207
All right. We're in. Bring another light.
We're cutting through pretty good.

1537
01:34:30.290 --> 01:34:33.293
There's some stuff in here
I ain't never seen.

1538
01:34:33.836 --> 01:34:36.129
All right. let's punch it down!

1539
01:34:37.381 --> 01:34:40.259
- Hey. Harry. did you see that?
- Yeah. Max. I see it. I see it. What is it?

1540
01:34:40.342 --> 01:34:43.846
- We lost the bite in the bit.
- All right. Back it off. Back it off.

1541
01:34:43.929 --> 01:34:45.305
Goddamn it!

1542
01:34:45.389 --> 01:34:47.558
Sounds like we twisted a shank.
Back it out of there. Max.

1543
01:34:47.641 --> 01:34:49.768
Good. Good. Hold over there.

1544
01:34:54.022 --> 01:34:57.150
Wow. this is
a goddamn Greek tragedy.

1545
01:34:57.276 --> 01:34:59.528
We've all seen
broken drill heads before.

1546
01:34:59.611 --> 01:35:01.363
Not after 10 feet.

1547
01:35:01.446 --> 01:35:04.116
- I never seen one.
- Well. now you've seen one.

1548
01:35:04.199 --> 01:35:06.743
- What do you want?
- Unpack the Judge.

1549
01:35:09.288 --> 01:35:10.622
Bear. Lev.

1550
01:35:11.748 --> 01:35:14.877
We're only three astronauts left now.

1551
01:35:15.460 --> 01:35:19.256
We're not astronauts. We're oil drillers.
We're not even supposed to be here.

1552
01:35:19.339 --> 01:35:21.884
What? You're not astronaut?

1553
01:35:21.967 --> 01:35:24.845
- I'm getting us out of here. Get in.
- Why?

1554
01:35:24.928 --> 01:35:27.264
Just get in the Armadillo.
I have an idea.

1555
01:35:27.347 --> 01:35:30.726
Houston. this is <i>Freedom.</i>
Do you copy? Houston. do you copy?

1556
01:35:30.809 --> 01:35:31.810
<i>Freedom</i> shuttle has...

1557
01:35:33.896 --> 01:35:35.230
We're getting some scattered
video feeds here

1558
01:35:35.314 --> 01:35:36.481
so we're gonna have to lead over.

1559
01:35:36.565 --> 01:35:38.692
<i>Houston. this is</i> Freedom.
<i>Do you copy?</i>

1560
01:35:39.276 --> 01:35:40.319
Thank God we have you. <i>Freedom.</i>

1561
01:35:40.402 --> 01:35:42.738
- <i>Freedom.</i> this is Houston. Go ahead.
- Don't lose them. Malloy.

1562
01:35:42.821 --> 01:35:43.989
<i>Sir. we're getting something.</i>

1563
01:35:44.072 --> 01:35:46.283
<i>Houston. this is</i> Freedom.
<i>We have landed safely.</i>

1564
01:35:46.366 --> 01:35:47.951
- <i>We are at site coordinates...</i>
- Where are they?

1565
01:35:48.035 --> 01:35:49.703
<i>...approximately 15H-32.</i>

1566
01:35:49.786 --> 01:35:51.747
Okay. I want to know everything
we can about that location.

1567
01:35:51.830 --> 01:35:52.831
- Got it.
- Get it before we lose them.

1568
01:35:52.915 --> 01:35:55.083
<i>We're also having electric
and antenna difficulties.</i>

1569
01:35:55.167 --> 01:35:56.460
Walter. get Mechanical on that.

1570
01:35:56.543 --> 01:35:58.420
<i>But we have commenced drilling.</i>

1571
01:35:58.503 --> 01:36:00.297
Stevens. we're losing him.
Bring it up on four.

1572
01:36:00.380 --> 01:36:01.423
- Come on.
- On four.

1573
01:36:01.506 --> 01:36:04.009
<i>Shuttle flight capability not yet known.</i>

1574
01:36:04.092 --> 01:36:05.093
- Bump the signal.
- Bumping.

1575
01:36:05.177 --> 01:36:06.595
Houston. Houston.

1576
01:36:06.678 --> 01:36:09.181
We lost them. Get them back.
Gruber. we need that hook-up.

1577
01:36:11.516 --> 01:36:14.686
I'll show you how we do things
where I come from.

1578
01:36:22.152 --> 01:36:23.362
Hold on!

1579
01:36:33.246 --> 01:36:34.498
Seat it.

1580
01:36:35.332 --> 01:36:37.918
All right. get ready. Max. thread it.

1581
01:36:39.461 --> 01:36:42.756
Guys. the clock is ticking.
Let's go. go. go. go. go!

1582
01:36:42.839 --> 01:36:44.883
All right! Good! Crank it loose!

1583
01:36:44.967 --> 01:36:47.886
Keep it at 25.
Let's kick a little asteroid butt!

1584
01:36:48.178 --> 01:36:51.598
All right. Chick. Give me more torque
on the turbine. huh?

1585
01:36:51.682 --> 01:36:53.141
Max. I need some more
power down here!

1586
01:36:53.225 --> 01:36:54.518
- All right. boss.
- Throw it forward.

1587
01:36:54.601 --> 01:36:55.769
then drop the hammer.

1588
01:36:55.852 --> 01:36:57.396
Let's drill through this turd.

1589
01:36:57.479 --> 01:36:59.940
Come on. boys. We gotta hop.
We're falling behind.

1590
01:37:00.023 --> 01:37:03.026
Dig. dig. dig. Chew this iron bitch up.

1591
01:37:08.323 --> 01:37:09.992
- Chick. the tranny is stuck.
- Harry!

1592
01:37:10.075 --> 01:37:12.995
- What is it?
- Chick. come on! Help!

1593
01:37:13.078 --> 01:37:14.830
- Release the clutch!
- Pull it up!

1594
01:37:14.913 --> 01:37:18.250
Okay. Well. this thing's not moving.

1595
01:37:18.333 --> 01:37:20.919
No. no. no! Shut it down! Shut it...

1596
01:37:28.427 --> 01:37:30.345
This is not working out. Harry.

1597
01:37:30.429 --> 01:37:34.558
- Are you all right?
- Blew the tranny. Blew the tranny.

1598
01:37:35.767 --> 01:37:37.227
Come on. God.

1599
01:37:38.603 --> 01:37:41.773
Just a little help. That's all I'm asking.

1600
01:37:42.441 --> 01:37:45.610
I think we're close enough.
He might've heard you.

1601
01:37:48.488 --> 01:37:51.033
Here's the bad news.
Before the asteroid passed the moon.

1602
01:37:51.116 --> 01:37:54.161
her rotation was stable
at 32 degrees on an X axis.

1603
01:37:54.244 --> 01:37:58.373
But now look at this.
The lunar gravity's put her in a spin.

1604
01:37:58.457 --> 01:38:02.044
She's tumbling on all three axes.
This wasn't expected. sir.

1605
01:38:02.127 --> 01:38:03.795
What does this do
for communications?

1606
01:38:03.879 --> 01:38:05.630
- Not good.
- We'll have definite contact

1607
01:38:05.714 --> 01:38:07.424
with the shuttle
for only seven more minutes.

1608
01:38:07.507 --> 01:38:10.260
- After that. it's radio darkness.
- For how long?

1609
01:38:10.343 --> 01:38:14.514
And after seven minutes.
we may never hear from them again.

1610
01:38:14.598 --> 01:38:17.225
But we're trying to bounce a signal
off a Russian military satellite.

1611
01:38:17.309 --> 01:38:18.602
reestablish contact that way.

1612
01:38:18.685 --> 01:38:20.562
If we lose the shuttle com.

1613
01:38:20.645 --> 01:38:23.106
when do we lose the ability
to remote detonate that nuke?

1614
01:38:23.190 --> 01:38:25.650
The weapon remote receives a signal
from a Milstar satellite.

1615
01:38:25.734 --> 01:38:27.736
Higher orbit. more powerful transmitter.

1616
01:38:27.819 --> 01:38:29.738
If we've got the shuttle
for seven minutes.

1617
01:38:29.821 --> 01:38:31.907
we can remote detonate
for an additional five.

1618
01:38:31.990 --> 01:38:33.075
What he's trying to say. General.

1619
01:38:33.158 --> 01:38:35.243
is that in 12 minutes' time
you may lose the ability

1620
01:38:35.327 --> 01:38:38.038
to detonate the nuke permanently.

1621
01:38:38.121 --> 01:38:40.123
I've got to inform the President.

1622
01:38:41.666 --> 01:38:44.211
Just want to make sure you know
we're stuck on an asteroid.

1623
01:38:44.294 --> 01:38:47.255
- Do you know what you're doing now?
- No. no. You know what?

1624
01:38:47.339 --> 01:38:49.591
I have no idea what I'm doing.
I have no idea.

1625
01:38:49.674 --> 01:38:52.010
This button.
I don't know what that does. okay?

1626
01:38:52.094 --> 01:38:54.596
All I know is
that we just crashed back there.

1627
01:38:54.679 --> 01:38:57.516
I lost two of my friends.
we're 25 miles from Harry's shuttle.

1628
01:38:57.599 --> 01:39:00.018
We don't know if he's alive.
We don't know if he can fly.

1629
01:39:00.102 --> 01:39:01.853
All I know is there's a beep
on this thing

1630
01:39:01.937 --> 01:39:03.230
and I'm trying to get us there.

1631
01:39:11.655 --> 01:39:13.532
Let's get it unpacked.

1632
01:39:14.825 --> 01:39:15.826
What's up?

1633
01:39:15.909 --> 01:39:18.703
We're drilling through some kind
of metal I've never seen before.

1634
01:39:18.787 --> 01:39:21.790
It's fried two of our drill bits.
and now we blew our first transmission.

1635
01:39:21.873 --> 01:39:22.833
So how deep are we?

1636
01:39:22.916 --> 01:39:24.584
We could use your help
with the transmission. Colonel.

1637
01:39:24.668 --> 01:39:27.587
I have an assessment report due now.
We're supposed to be at 200 feet.

1638
01:39:27.671 --> 01:39:29.464
So how deep are we?

1639
01:39:29.548 --> 01:39:32.008
Not as deep as we'll be when you quit
asking me all these questions

1640
01:39:32.092 --> 01:39:33.760
and help us load this transmission on.

1641
01:39:33.844 --> 01:39:35.011
What is our current depth?

1642
01:39:35.095 --> 01:39:36.888
Our current depth
is not important. Colonel.

1643
01:39:36.972 --> 01:39:40.016
I'll decide what's important.
We've got 800 feet to drill.

1644
01:39:40.100 --> 01:39:43.103
You've had two and a half hours.
Where are we?

1645
01:39:44.646 --> 01:39:47.691
We're at 57 feet.
Now. if you're not too busy.

1646
01:39:47.774 --> 01:39:50.485
maybe you can give us a hand
with this transmission.

1647
01:39:50.569 --> 01:39:55.824
Colonel Sharp! Get this wrapped up.
I'll be right back. Colonel Sharp!

1648
01:39:55.907 --> 01:39:58.326
All right. I'm coming through.
We have contact. Over.

1649
01:39:59.161 --> 01:40:02.497
That's as clear as it's gonna get.

1650
01:40:02.581 --> 01:40:04.332
Houston. this is <i>Freedom.</i>
Do you copy?

1651
01:40:04.749 --> 01:40:08.503
<i>Working at a remote satellite link
at this moment. Transmission change.</i>

1652
01:40:08.587 --> 01:40:09.629
- Colonel!
- Twenty minutes.

1653
01:40:09.713 --> 01:40:11.590
Puts drilling final at 10 hours.

1654
01:40:11.673 --> 01:40:13.842
Please advise.
That's four hours past the zero barrier.

1655
01:40:13.925 --> 01:40:15.177
<i>Please advise.</i>

1656
01:40:15.260 --> 01:40:18.180
What the hell is this? "Zero depth"?

1657
01:40:18.263 --> 01:40:19.306
And where'd this come from?

1658
01:40:19.389 --> 01:40:20.974
Who are you talking to?
Is that Truman?

1659
01:40:21.057 --> 01:40:22.517
Let me have that phone.
Give me the phone.

1660
01:40:22.601 --> 01:40:25.520
Truman! Look. this is what happens
when you drill.

1661
01:40:25.604 --> 01:40:29.858
We cannot use your "U.S. Air Force
Personnel Only" drill time card.

1662
01:40:29.941 --> 01:40:31.359
Who wrote this thing. by the way?

1663
01:40:31.443 --> 01:40:33.445
- We're losing come again.
- Look... Is he getting this?

1664
01:40:33.528 --> 01:40:34.779
Does he hear me or...
What's wrong with this?

1665
01:40:34.863 --> 01:40:35.864
<i>The com's down.</i>

1666
01:40:35.947 --> 01:40:37.032
<i>What do you mean.
"The com's down"?</i>

1667
01:40:37.115 --> 01:40:39.618
<i>What do I mean? I mean we've lost
communication to mission control.</i>

1668
01:40:39.701 --> 01:40:42.287
Fine. Let's go back to the cargo bay
and get the transmission.

1669
01:40:42.370 --> 01:40:44.206
Hey. Harry. guess what.
You had your shot. You didn't do it.

1670
01:40:44.414 --> 01:40:46.041
<i>You understand me? You can't...</i>

1671
01:40:46.124 --> 01:40:48.543
<i>Why don't you stay here
and take your little drill card...</i>

1672
01:40:49.961 --> 01:40:52.589
Write a report. why don't you?
That'll be a...

1673
01:40:53.715 --> 01:40:56.009
My men and I will go
and get this hole dug!

1674
01:40:56.092 --> 01:41:00.055
You and your men are the biggest
mistake in the history of NASA.

1675
01:41:02.307 --> 01:41:04.809
- We've lost communication.
- God.

1676
01:41:07.938 --> 01:41:11.066
We're not looking too good right now.

1677
01:41:11.149 --> 01:41:14.819
No shit.
We gotta get that radio back up.

1678
01:41:17.239 --> 01:41:20.408
Mr President.
it's time to make a decision.

1679
01:41:20.492 --> 01:41:24.329
We can remote detonate the bomb
for only another five minutes.

1680
01:41:26.831 --> 01:41:30.752
Yes? Kimsey here. Yes. Mr President.

1681
01:41:30.835 --> 01:41:32.837
Yes. we saw that. too. sir.

1682
01:41:33.630 --> 01:41:36.258
But maybe we should wait until they...

1683
01:41:42.847 --> 01:41:47.727
Dan. get them out of there.
Evac right now.

1684
01:41:47.811 --> 01:41:49.229
What's going on here?

1685
01:41:49.312 --> 01:41:51.022
I've been ordered
to override the system.

1686
01:41:55.944 --> 01:41:57.696
Well. what is this?

1687
01:42:02.409 --> 01:42:04.160
Secondary protocol.

1688
01:42:10.458 --> 01:42:13.295
But they haven't drilled
the damn hole yet!

1689
01:42:17.340 --> 01:42:19.551
The President's advisors
feel that the drilling isn't working.

1690
01:42:19.634 --> 01:42:21.428
And we've lost radio contact.
maybe for good.

1691
01:42:21.511 --> 01:42:23.305
We've only got a few minutes
left of guaranteed ability

1692
01:42:23.388 --> 01:42:24.639
to remote detonate that nuke.

1693
01:42:24.723 --> 01:42:26.141
If we don't do it now
we could lose control.

1694
01:42:26.224 --> 01:42:27.392
and we may never get it back.

1695
01:42:27.475 --> 01:42:30.562
Well. you tell the President that
he better fire his so-called advisors.

1696
01:42:30.645 --> 01:42:32.397
And if you detonate that nuke
on the surface.

1697
01:42:32.480 --> 01:42:34.024
we waste a perfectly good bomb

1698
01:42:34.107 --> 01:42:36.067
and we have one chance
to save this planet!

1699
01:42:46.995 --> 01:42:48.913
I need that radio.

1700
01:42:48.997 --> 01:42:51.124
<i>Gruber. give me everything
you got now!</i>

1701
01:42:51.207 --> 01:42:52.250
Roger that.

1702
01:42:55.795 --> 01:42:57.505
Yes. Mr President.
I understand that completely.

1703
01:42:57.589 --> 01:42:59.549
but my point is very. very simple.

1704
01:42:59.632 --> 01:43:02.260
And I think you need to trust me on this
because I know something about it.

1705
01:43:02.344 --> 01:43:05.180
I guarantee you. if you do this.
you kill us all.

1706
01:43:09.267 --> 01:43:11.144
Yes. sir.

1707
01:43:11.227 --> 01:43:13.563
General. he wants you.

1708
01:43:15.899 --> 01:43:18.234
This is Kimsey. Yes. sir.

1709
01:43:19.110 --> 01:43:20.612
I understand.

1710
01:43:23.615 --> 01:43:27.118
The orders are
to remote detonate in 30 seconds.

1711
01:43:27.202 --> 01:43:29.788
You have not told them yet!

1712
01:43:29.871 --> 01:43:32.499
That is my father up there!

1713
01:43:32.582 --> 01:43:33.958
This is one order you shouldn't follow.

1714
01:43:34.042 --> 01:43:35.877
- and you fucking know it!
- No! Don't touch me!

1715
01:43:35.960 --> 01:43:37.837
Let her go. Let her go!

1716
01:43:40.965 --> 01:43:42.467
Your key. sir.

1717
01:43:47.514 --> 01:43:49.140
God be with them.

1718
01:43:50.308 --> 01:43:51.434
Slow it down.

1719
01:43:58.650 --> 01:44:03.822
Harry. the clock on that nine-foot
nuclear weapon is ticking.

1720
01:44:05.490 --> 01:44:09.411
Oh. my God! Sharp!
Get back here now!

1721
01:44:10.412 --> 01:44:12.497
Watts. get the shuttle ready
to evac now!

1722
01:44:12.580 --> 01:44:13.998
It just came on all by itself.

1723
01:44:14.082 --> 01:44:15.500
- What... What the hell's happening?
- Secondary protocol.

1724
01:44:15.583 --> 01:44:17.669
- What's that? What?
- Secondary protocol.

1725
01:44:17.752 --> 01:44:19.421
- What does that mean?
- What the hell's secondary protocol?

1726
01:44:19.504 --> 01:44:20.547
They're detonating this thing
from Earth.

1727
01:44:20.630 --> 01:44:22.757
What do you mean. detonating?
We haven't even drilled the hole yet!

1728
01:44:22.841 --> 01:44:24.134
- What are you talking about?
- The hole? Whoa. whoa!

1729
01:44:24.217 --> 01:44:25.260
Get your helmets on now.

1730
01:44:25.343 --> 01:44:26.511
No. no. How... How you turn it off?

1731
01:44:26.594 --> 01:44:28.263
Colonel Sharp.
I got two men out on that rock.

1732
01:44:28.346 --> 01:44:30.723
I got a man out there. too.
We gotta evac now!

1733
01:44:30.807 --> 01:44:32.767
Max. Rockhound.
get back to the shuttle. double-time!

1734
01:44:32.851 --> 01:44:34.185
They could be on their way here.

1735
01:44:34.269 --> 01:44:35.728
They're not on their way here.

1736
01:44:35.812 --> 01:44:38.523
They would've talked to us by now.
We would've seen them.

1737
01:44:38.606 --> 01:44:41.693
- Watts. air lock the cockpit now!
- I copy you.

1738
01:44:41.901 --> 01:44:43.695
- Max. Rockhound!
- Hey. wait a minute!

1739
01:44:43.778 --> 01:44:45.155
- How do you turn this thing off?
- Max. Rockhound...

1740
01:44:46.531 --> 01:44:48.700
- Harry. do you copy?
- Something's wrong.

1741
01:44:48.783 --> 01:44:51.619
Yeah. it's all wrong. man.
We shouldn't even be up here.

1742
01:44:51.703 --> 01:44:53.538
I know. Let's go back to the ship!

1743
01:44:54.831 --> 01:44:56.624
I'm not leaving without my men. Sharp.

1744
01:44:56.708 --> 01:44:59.419
We've got two and a half minutes
to drop it and get off this rock.

1745
01:44:59.502 --> 01:45:01.963
If they're not back by the time we finish.
we leave without them.

1746
01:45:02.046 --> 01:45:04.424
Okay. let's simplify this.
Let's just turn the bomb off right now.

1747
01:45:04.507 --> 01:45:07.218
If we don't put this bomb down in a hole
800 feet onto a fault line.

1748
01:45:07.302 --> 01:45:09.721
all you're gonna have
is a real expensive fireworks show.

1749
01:45:09.804 --> 01:45:12.223
This is turning
into a surrealistic nightmare here.

1750
01:45:12.724 --> 01:45:14.976
Watsler. are you listening? It's Truman.

1751
01:45:15.059 --> 01:45:18.980
Okay. listen to me carefully.
I want you to kill it. Kill the uplink.

1752
01:45:30.241 --> 01:45:32.869
- Give us the time. Sharp.
- Shut this bomb down now!

1753
01:45:32.952 --> 01:45:34.704
- It's not my call.
- Then whose call is it?

1754
01:45:34.787 --> 01:45:36.331
An order to detonate can only come
from the President.

1755
01:45:36.414 --> 01:45:37.957
- The President's not here!
- Let's just turn it off now.

1756
01:45:38.041 --> 01:45:39.083
You've gotta give us more time!

1757
01:45:39.167 --> 01:45:40.877
I'm telling you
to shut this bomb down now!

1758
01:45:40.960 --> 01:45:42.504
And I'm telling you it's not my call!

1759
01:45:42.587 --> 01:45:44.506
Well. guess what.
I just made the call for you.

1760
01:45:44.589 --> 01:45:46.007
Harry!

1761
01:45:47.884 --> 01:45:50.970
Don't. You could set it off.

1762
01:45:51.054 --> 01:45:54.474
Man. What are you doing
with a gun in space?

1763
01:45:57.936 --> 01:46:01.064
Come on. Come on.
We gotta stop that bomb right now.

1764
01:46:01.147 --> 01:46:02.482
Kill the uplink.

1765
01:46:02.899 --> 01:46:06.736
This thing is gonna blow.
We gotta get it off the ship.

1766
01:46:06.819 --> 01:46:09.197
- Easy.
- Stand down. Sergeant.

1767
01:46:09.280 --> 01:46:13.201
Shut this bomb down
and let us finish our job the right way.

1768
01:46:13.284 --> 01:46:16.037
I'm under orders
to protect a surface detonation.

1769
01:46:16.120 --> 01:46:18.456
I'm gonna give you three seconds
to shut this bomb down.

1770
01:46:18.540 --> 01:46:21.042
and then I'm gonna make you
shoot me.

1771
01:46:21.125 --> 01:46:23.878
Hurry. Watsler.
For Christ's sake. hurry.

1772
01:46:27.632 --> 01:46:29.133
What happened?

1773
01:46:33.805 --> 01:46:37.141
Sir. the override... It's been overridden.

1774
01:46:38.309 --> 01:46:39.435
I've bought us a couple of minutes.

1775
01:46:39.519 --> 01:46:41.563
so get that radio working. okay?
Hurry. hurry!

1776
01:46:44.148 --> 01:46:47.110
Bring me all the way up here
just to blow me and my friends up?

1777
01:46:47.193 --> 01:46:48.653
Is that it?

1778
01:46:48.736 --> 01:46:50.697
- Listen...
- Shut up!

1779
01:46:50.780 --> 01:46:53.199
Shut up. Colonel. I'm talking now.

1780
01:46:54.867 --> 01:46:58.037
It could start again.
It might've been a warning.

1781
01:46:59.956 --> 01:47:02.417
That's why you are gonna dismantle
this bomb.

1782
01:47:02.500 --> 01:47:04.836
All right. What'd we miss?

1783
01:47:09.674 --> 01:47:11.676
- Do it again.
- Go.

1784
01:47:15.930 --> 01:47:17.348
Keep trying.

1785
01:47:19.100 --> 01:47:23.563
Sir. I need you to cease and desist.
I need your terminal now.

1786
01:47:26.691 --> 01:47:29.944
- They're reactivating the bomb.
- Coming back on-line. sir.

1787
01:47:30.028 --> 01:47:33.323
Oh. geez. Here we go again.

1788
01:47:33.406 --> 01:47:34.616
What are you doing up here?

1789
01:47:34.699 --> 01:47:36.367
And why did you even bother
to make the trip?

1790
01:47:36.451 --> 01:47:39.370
To do the right thing.
to see that it's done.

1791
01:47:47.086 --> 01:47:49.964
For God's sakes.
think about what you're doing.

1792
01:47:50.048 --> 01:47:53.593
Why are you listening to someone
that's 100.000 miles away?

1793
01:47:53.676 --> 01:47:57.180
We're here.
Nobody down there can help us.

1794
01:47:57.263 --> 01:48:01.225
So if we don't get this job done.
then everybody's gone.

1795
01:48:01.309 --> 01:48:02.685
One minute.

1796
01:48:03.770 --> 01:48:06.564
I've been drilling holes in the Earth
for 30 years.

1797
01:48:06.648 --> 01:48:11.277
And I have never. never missed
a depth that I have aimed for.

1798
01:48:11.361 --> 01:48:14.906
And by God. I am not gonna miss
this one. I will make 800 feet.

1799
01:48:14.989 --> 01:48:16.366
42 seconds.

1800
01:48:18.076 --> 01:48:21.162
But I can't do it alone. Colonel.
I need your help.

1801
01:48:21.245 --> 01:48:24.707
You swear on your daughter's life.
on my family's

1802
01:48:24.791 --> 01:48:27.335
that you can hit that mark?

1803
01:48:27.418 --> 01:48:31.798
I will make 800 feet.
I swear to God. I will.

1804
01:48:31.881 --> 01:48:34.092
Then let's turn this bomb off.

1805
01:48:46.229 --> 01:48:47.897
Steady. Steady. Take it back.

1806
01:48:47.980 --> 01:48:49.941
That's what you'll have to do.
Get them off backwards.

1807
01:48:50.024 --> 01:48:52.819
- Rainbow track? Under one? Under...
- All of them. All of them. All of them!

1808
01:48:52.902 --> 01:48:56.781
- Okay. Okay. Are we free of static?
- Do a good job. Do a good job.

1809
01:48:56.864 --> 01:48:58.199
- Steady. Steady.
- Good job.

1810
01:48:58.282 --> 01:49:00.576
- All right. All right. All right.
- Go! Go! Go!

1811
01:49:00.660 --> 01:49:03.454
Red wire "A." Ready? And now.

1812
01:49:03.538 --> 01:49:06.082
Come on! Come on!
Come on! Come on!

1813
01:49:06.165 --> 01:49:10.169
- Negative "B." Ready. and now.
- Do a good job. Do a good job.

1814
01:49:10.253 --> 01:49:12.547
- Track flipped. Hots in.
- It better be. Go.

1815
01:49:12.630 --> 01:49:14.006
Red or blue?

1816
01:49:16.300 --> 01:49:17.468
Wait...

1817
01:49:22.724 --> 01:49:23.808
Blue.

1818
01:49:27.186 --> 01:49:29.647
- Good job!
- You got it.

1819
01:49:33.651 --> 01:49:36.154
God. it sucks up here.

1820
01:49:36.988 --> 01:49:39.699
Sir. the clock has stopped
at three seconds.

1821
01:49:39.782 --> 01:49:40.783
What?

1822
01:49:41.701 --> 01:49:45.079
- Have we lost complete radio contact?
- I got some magic happening.

1823
01:49:45.163 --> 01:49:46.456
We're bouncing off Russian
and French satellites.

1824
01:49:46.539 --> 01:49:50.626
- It may have a faint signal.
- <i>Houston? Houston. do you copy?</i>

1825
01:49:52.295 --> 01:49:53.963
<i>Go ahead.</i> Freedom.

1826
01:49:54.714 --> 01:49:57.425
Houston. you have a problem...
Problem.

1827
01:49:57.508 --> 01:50:00.011
See. I promised my little girl
that I'd be coming home.

1828
01:50:01.345 --> 01:50:04.140
Now. I don't know
what you people are doing down there.

1829
01:50:04.223 --> 01:50:05.850
but we got a hole to dig up here.

1830
01:50:07.602 --> 01:50:09.437
Go. go. go. go!
Come on. We got work to do.

1831
01:50:09.979 --> 01:50:13.441
Okay. guys. All go. no quit.
How you doing down there? Good?

1832
01:50:13.524 --> 01:50:16.402
Okay. got the tranny.
We're back in business.

1833
01:50:16.486 --> 01:50:20.198
Hey. you guys should take a break
and come up and see this.

1834
01:50:21.616 --> 01:50:24.452
Wow. Got a great view
of the Earth from here.

1835
01:50:24.535 --> 01:50:26.496
Too bad we'll never set foot
on her again.

1836
01:50:26.579 --> 01:50:29.123
- Lev. do you see anything?
- No.

1837
01:50:29.207 --> 01:50:31.000
Well. keep going. I'm not giving up.

1838
01:50:32.543 --> 01:50:34.420
Hold up here. Bear.

1839
01:50:34.504 --> 01:50:36.631
- Oh. boy.
- This is great.

1840
01:50:36.714 --> 01:50:39.550
We just happen to run
into the Grand Canyon on the asteroid?

1841
01:50:39.634 --> 01:50:43.054
I told you.
you took a wrong way. a wrong road.

1842
01:50:43.137 --> 01:50:46.474
What... What road?
Do you see any roads around here?

1843
01:50:46.557 --> 01:50:50.561
You know what? I do not have
much pleasure being near God's ear.

1844
01:50:50.645 --> 01:50:53.147
But you think this is looking good.
or what?

1845
01:50:53.231 --> 01:50:57.735
Lev. why don't you just do humanity
a favour and just shut the hell up?

1846
01:51:02.740 --> 01:51:04.617
Have you ever heard of Evel Knievel?

1847
01:51:04.700 --> 01:51:07.036
No. I never saw <i>Star Wars.</i>

1848
01:51:13.042 --> 01:51:15.503
All right. Doing a good job.

1849
01:51:15.586 --> 01:51:18.422
- Give me a depth reading. Max.
- We're 150 feet. Harry.

1850
01:51:23.761 --> 01:51:25.221
Ride them. cowboy!

1851
01:51:27.598 --> 01:51:31.853
Get off the nuclear warhead.

1852
01:51:31.936 --> 01:51:33.938
I was doing that guy
from that movie. you know.

1853
01:51:34.021 --> 01:51:37.108
Slim Pickens. where he rides it
all the way in the nuclear warhead.

1854
01:51:37.191 --> 01:51:40.069
- Now.
- You didn't see that one. huh?

1855
01:51:40.152 --> 01:51:43.030
We got 700 feet of hole
to dig. Rockhound.

1856
01:51:43.114 --> 01:51:47.618
All right. Just... Just wanted to feel
the power between my legs. brother.

1857
01:51:48.786 --> 01:51:50.121
Hey. Sharp.

1858
01:51:50.872 --> 01:51:53.791
No nukes! No nukes! No nukes!

1859
01:51:53.875 --> 01:51:55.835
You got any more bullets
in that gun. Sharp?

1860
01:51:56.168 --> 01:51:57.253
What did Watts tell you. Bear?

1861
01:51:57.336 --> 01:51:59.088
If she kicked you in the balls.
you'd keep floating.

1862
01:51:59.171 --> 01:52:00.256
Yeah.

1863
01:52:02.550 --> 01:52:03.718
We turn the thrusters off.

1864
01:52:03.801 --> 01:52:06.012
we jump this thing.
we float right over it.

1865
01:52:07.388 --> 01:52:09.223
Go over it again. Lev.

1866
01:52:09.307 --> 01:52:12.768
Throw the jet thrusters off
exactly when we jump.

1867
01:52:12.852 --> 01:52:14.353
- And then we're gonna put them on...
- Okay.

1868
01:52:14.437 --> 01:52:16.480
...and we gonna go down nice and slow.

1869
01:52:16.564 --> 01:52:20.067
- That's it. That's it. baby. That's it.
- Is this gonna work?

1870
01:52:20.151 --> 01:52:24.322
- I don't know.
- Lev. you know what. just lie to me.

1871
01:52:24.405 --> 01:52:30.411
Let's say 50... No.
More like. like 70-30 or 80-20.

1872
01:52:30.494 --> 01:52:34.665
But you know what? If it works.
the two of you gonna be heroes.

1873
01:52:34.790 --> 01:52:35.917
just like me.

1874
01:52:36.000 --> 01:52:38.753
Screw it.
We're jumping over this canyon.

1875
01:52:42.965 --> 01:52:45.885
Just for the record.
this is a very bad idea!

1876
01:52:49.430 --> 01:52:50.556
Wait for the edge now.

1877
01:52:50.640 --> 01:52:52.850
- Wait till we get there. Wait...
- I'm waiting.

1878
01:52:53.684 --> 01:52:59.440
- Here we come. Now. not till we do it.
- Three. two. one!

1879
01:52:59.523 --> 01:53:01.025
Off!

1880
01:53:09.283 --> 01:53:10.910
- Yes!
- It's working!

1881
01:53:10.993 --> 01:53:12.119
It's working!

1882
01:53:12.203 --> 01:53:15.164
- Oh. my God!
- Yeah!

1883
01:53:15.247 --> 01:53:20.503
- I'm a genius! Wait a minute.
- Whoa. Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa!

1884
01:53:20.586 --> 01:53:22.797
- We got some rocks!
- Go left! Go left!

1885
01:53:22.880 --> 01:53:25.299
Lev! Lev. I can't do anything!

1886
01:53:25.383 --> 01:53:26.550
Turn!

1887
01:53:35.101 --> 01:53:38.229
Okay. okay.
we're floating into outer space.

1888
01:53:38.312 --> 01:53:40.272
- Check main switch.
- This could be a little bit of a problem.

1889
01:53:41.524 --> 01:53:44.485
- Thrusters on. Now!
- All right. turn them on.

1890
01:53:46.862 --> 01:53:48.698
- What's wrong?
- I... I don't know.

1891
01:53:48.781 --> 01:53:52.118
The... The thrusters not working.
I hate this machine!

1892
01:53:52.201 --> 01:53:53.202
I thought you had this planned!

1893
01:53:53.285 --> 01:53:54.996
- Be quiet! I must think!
- What're we supposed to do?

1894
01:53:55.079 --> 01:53:57.999
- I'm stepping outside.
- You're... You're going outside?

1895
01:53:58.082 --> 01:54:03.587
I am the only certified astronaut.
and I'm saving your American ass!

1896
01:54:07.633 --> 01:54:09.677
Yes. You'll listen to him. Right.

1897
01:54:15.182 --> 01:54:19.061
Hurry up. Lev. because we're
about a mile off the asteroid!

1898
01:54:19.145 --> 01:54:22.523
Just a second. The fuel line is iced up.

1899
01:54:22.606 --> 01:54:26.569
- Yeah. I think maybe working now.
- No. Lev. it's not working!

1900
01:54:26.652 --> 01:54:29.530
I'm sorry. A.J.. I was way off the odds.

1901
01:54:29.613 --> 01:54:31.157
We're getting higher. man.

1902
01:54:31.240 --> 01:54:34.368
Look out! The rocks! Rocks are coming!

1903
01:54:40.791 --> 01:54:42.043
Hold on!

1904
01:54:46.672 --> 01:54:49.467
- Pull the thrusters!
- Lev. look out!

1905
01:54:56.515 --> 01:54:58.267
- We lost Lev.
- A.J.!

1906
01:54:59.769 --> 01:55:02.146
A.J.. the thrusters!

1907
01:55:06.150 --> 01:55:07.943
Let's get Lev back!

1908
01:55:16.452 --> 01:55:18.871
Lev. hold on! We're coming in!

1909
01:55:35.846 --> 01:55:37.556
Thank you. Jesus. Thank you. Lord.

1910
01:55:37.640 --> 01:55:39.600
Thank you. Thank you. thank you.
thank you. thank you.

1911
01:55:42.144 --> 01:55:47.399
- Lev!
- Now I'm really a Russian hero!

1912
01:55:47.483 --> 01:55:49.568
- I told you!
- I know!

1913
01:55:49.652 --> 01:55:52.613
- I knew this would work!
- Good odds. you know?

1914
01:55:52.696 --> 01:55:55.324
Come on. Lev.
Get in here. We gotta go.

1915
01:55:59.537 --> 01:56:01.831
Rockhound. keep an eye
on that transmission.

1916
01:56:01.914 --> 01:56:05.042
- Tranny looks good. Harry.
- All right. Take it out of there.

1917
01:56:05.126 --> 01:56:06.919
Lock it down. Chick.

1918
01:56:08.754 --> 01:56:09.880
Nice.

1919
01:56:11.215 --> 01:56:14.635
How come we didn't get any training
on this thing?

1920
01:56:14.718 --> 01:56:19.431
Whoa. Very cool. I could take out
this asteroid single-handedly.

1921
01:56:19.515 --> 01:56:22.726
Okay. boys. give it a rest.
I'll take it from here.

1922
01:56:22.810 --> 01:56:24.395
Whoa!

1923
01:56:24.478 --> 01:56:26.313
- What the hell is that?
- It's Rockhound.

1924
01:56:26.397 --> 01:56:29.191
Whoa. This is so much fun. it's freaky.

1925
01:56:31.235 --> 01:56:32.570
Rockhound!

1926
01:56:33.571 --> 01:56:36.115
Whoa. watch your heads.
Sorry. Harry.

1927
01:56:38.534 --> 01:56:40.953
- Out of my way. boys!
- Rockhound!

1928
01:56:41.036 --> 01:56:43.080
Meet your maker. asteroid!

1929
01:56:47.543 --> 01:56:50.004
What the hell's the matter
with you. Rockhound?

1930
01:56:50.087 --> 01:56:51.797
- This is insane.
- Goddamn!

1931
01:56:51.881 --> 01:56:55.509
- Have you lost your mind?
- He's got space dementia.

1932
01:56:55.593 --> 01:56:57.553
Harry. you ought to watch your man.

1933
01:57:00.306 --> 01:57:04.101
Max. downshift slowly
and put it in reverse.

1934
01:57:04.185 --> 01:57:06.729
We gotta get that pipe out of there.

1935
01:57:09.690 --> 01:57:10.900
What's happening?

1936
01:57:10.983 --> 01:57:13.485
- The ground's cracking!
- Earthquake!

1937
01:57:21.702 --> 01:57:23.454
Quick. shut it off!

1938
01:57:24.747 --> 01:57:28.209
- Shut it off! Shut it off now!
- We're gonna have a blowout!

1939
01:57:28.292 --> 01:57:31.545
- We hit a gas pocket!
- We got pressure out the ass!

1940
01:57:33.255 --> 01:57:37.051
Max. get your helmet on!
Max. it's gonna blow!

1941
01:57:37.134 --> 01:57:40.095
- Jesus. I'm cooking!
- Max. get out of there!

1942
01:57:40.179 --> 01:57:41.555
This is it!

1943
01:57:43.015 --> 01:57:44.975
Harry!

1944
01:57:46.977 --> 01:57:48.395
I'm bailing!

1945
01:57:52.024 --> 01:57:53.567
Max!

1946
01:57:56.320 --> 01:57:59.323
- Goodbye. Max.
- Max!

1947
01:57:59.406 --> 01:58:00.741
Take care. buddy.

1948
01:58:00.824 --> 01:58:03.077
- Armadillo's off the scope.
- I think we've had a blowout.

1949
01:58:03.160 --> 01:58:06.538
- No sign of the Armadillo.
- Somebody punch up the Armadillo.

1950
01:58:36.193 --> 01:58:37.987
Get a hold of Truman.

1951
01:58:39.863 --> 01:58:41.657
Prepare the world for bad news.

1952
01:58:49.290 --> 01:58:50.833
<i>We're getting sketchy information</i>

1953
01:58:50.916 --> 01:58:54.128
<i>that the mission
has suffered massive failure.</i>

1954
01:58:54.211 --> 01:58:56.797
<i>And what we're trying to do right now
is to confirm that</i>

1955
01:58:56.880 --> 01:58:58.382
<i>and find out exactly what that means.</i>

1956
01:58:58.465 --> 01:59:01.635
<i>Repeat. we're getting leaks
from several NASA officials.</i>

1957
01:59:01.719 --> 01:59:03.470
<i>some rushing home to be
with their families.</i>

1958
01:59:03.554 --> 01:59:06.849
<i>that the drilling was unsuccessful.</i>

1959
01:59:16.066 --> 01:59:18.610
This could very well be our final hour.

1960
01:59:22.531 --> 01:59:26.702
<i>We're gonna go off the air now.
Good luck and God bless.</i>

1961
01:59:31.081 --> 01:59:32.958
- We've got incoming.
- I got tracks.

1962
01:59:33.042 --> 01:59:35.627
NORAD's tracking four small incoming
over Europe.

1963
01:59:35.711 --> 01:59:37.087
They think one's about
to hit near Paris.

1964
02:00:03.447 --> 02:00:04.865
<i>Reports are coming in...</i>

1965
02:00:04.948 --> 02:00:07.534
<i>Martial law has been implemented
in 42 countries.</i>

1966
02:00:07.618 --> 02:00:10.079
<i>Once the asteroid hits zero barrier.</i>

1967
02:00:10.162 --> 02:00:14.458
<i>it will take about three hours
and 57 minutes to impact Earth.</i>

1968
02:00:18.504 --> 02:00:21.131
Well. I guess we do it
the President's way. I'll order an evac.

1969
02:00:21.215 --> 02:00:22.466
You can remote detonate.

1970
02:00:22.549 --> 02:00:24.134
You still don't think this'll work.
do you?

1971
02:00:24.218 --> 02:00:25.928
Well. what I think is irrelevant.

1972
02:00:26.011 --> 02:00:29.139
- We need to do it now.
- Fine.

1973
02:00:29.223 --> 02:00:31.350
- Can they still take off?
- We hope so.

1974
02:00:31.475 --> 02:00:33.644
You are the one
that pulled them into this!

1975
02:00:33.727 --> 02:00:37.106
That is my family up there.
so I don't wanna hear. "We hope so!"

1976
02:00:42.653 --> 02:00:45.739
Guess what. guys?
It's time to embrace the horror.

1977
02:00:46.490 --> 02:00:49.952
Look. We got front-row tickets
to the end of the Earth.

1978
02:01:12.182 --> 02:01:16.270
- Yeah! Way to go. baby!
- Harry!

1979
02:01:21.859 --> 02:01:25.571
- Yeah!
- Yo. Harry! What's up. baby?

1980
02:01:25.654 --> 02:01:29.116
Hey. get that bomb out of there!
We got a hole to make!

1981
02:01:29.700 --> 02:01:34.455
<i>Houston. you're not gonna believe this.
but the other Armadillo has arrived.</i>

1982
02:01:34.538 --> 02:01:38.292
All right. people. listen up.
Settle down and focus.

1983
02:01:38.375 --> 02:01:40.669
- Mechanical. get on-line.
- P.P.O.. give me a set-up.

1984
02:01:40.752 --> 02:01:42.629
Your boyfriend's back.

1985
02:01:43.213 --> 02:01:45.841
- Yo. Harry!
- You're awesome. baby!

1986
02:01:47.217 --> 02:01:49.136
Hey. Harry. You miss me?

1987
02:01:49.219 --> 02:01:52.764
A.J.. I got just five words for you.

1988
02:01:52.848 --> 02:01:55.976
- Damn glad to see you. boy!
- That's six words.

1989
02:01:56.059 --> 02:01:59.104
- Chick. walk them down.
- So where's this hole you need dug?

1990
02:01:59.646 --> 02:02:02.232
<i>Houston. drilling has recommenced.</i>

1991
02:02:02.316 --> 02:02:05.903
Do you think they can drill 250 feet
in an hour?

1992
02:02:05.986 --> 02:02:07.404
They better.

1993
02:02:07.821 --> 02:02:10.032
Bring that piece on in. Bear.

1994
02:02:10.574 --> 02:02:12.075
Tractor pull.

1995
02:02:12.868 --> 02:02:16.705
- I'm coming down!
- We got 250 feet to go.

1996
02:02:16.788 --> 02:02:19.708
It's our last transmission.
last drill head.

1997
02:02:19.791 --> 02:02:23.295
Punch it through.
First gear. We got contact.

1998
02:02:24.046 --> 02:02:25.923
Drive it on down. A.J.

1999
02:02:27.633 --> 02:02:30.677
- I got this. man. Let's go!
- Lev. the right engine hub.

2000
02:02:30.761 --> 02:02:33.096
Houston. I'm getting no response
from the pref light sequence.

2001
02:02:33.180 --> 02:02:36.683
Come on now. This is not...
Hey. Hey. come here.

2002
02:02:36.767 --> 02:02:39.978
Can you get me out of here.
please. Lev? Thank you.

2003
02:02:41.980 --> 02:02:43.982
- Jesus! Hey!
- Wait...

2004
02:02:44.066 --> 02:02:45.275
- <i>Lev. the right engine...</i>
- Okay.

2005
02:02:45.359 --> 02:02:47.027
Let me out of here. will you?

2006
02:02:47.110 --> 02:02:49.738
Just trying to have some fun
before I die!

2007
02:02:49.821 --> 02:02:53.575
- How deep are we?
- 770.

2008
02:02:58.789 --> 02:03:00.832
- Whoa. they got problems.
- The gauges are spiking.

2009
02:03:00.916 --> 02:03:03.126
Methane! Shut it down! Back it down!

2010
02:03:03.210 --> 02:03:05.128
I can't pull back now.
The bit will get lodged.

2011
02:03:05.212 --> 02:03:07.214
We don't have enough time!

2012
02:03:07.297 --> 02:03:10.968
- Whoa. whoa. whoa! It's gonna blow!
- It's how we lost Max!

2013
02:03:11.051 --> 02:03:13.303
I know what I'm talking about.
We can punch through this.

2014
02:03:13.387 --> 02:03:14.888
We can knock this out of the park.

2015
02:03:14.972 --> 02:03:17.474
- This is our last transmission. A.J.
- Goddamn it!

2016
02:03:17.558 --> 02:03:22.145
If you're ever gonna trust me. ever.
once in your life. trust me now!

2017
02:03:22.229 --> 02:03:23.897
Harry. it's gonna blow!

2018
02:03:23.981 --> 02:03:27.442
Harry. I know what I'm doing.
You just gotta trust me.

2019
02:03:28.527 --> 02:03:30.028
Make the call.

2020
02:03:32.698 --> 02:03:35.617
All right. Hold on.
I'm pushing through her.

2021
02:03:40.872 --> 02:03:42.874
I'm pushing through her!

2022
02:03:43.584 --> 02:03:46.795
- What's your depth?
- 775. 780.

2023
02:03:46.878 --> 02:03:49.131
Dig it up. baby! Ram it home!

2024
02:03:50.173 --> 02:03:51.550
Drive on down. A.J.!

2025
02:03:51.633 --> 02:03:54.261
Seven-eighty-five. Come on. Come on.

2026
02:03:54.344 --> 02:03:56.263
- Come on. A.J.!
- Punch it!

2027
02:03:56.346 --> 02:03:57.431
Ninety-one. Come on.

2028
02:03:57.514 --> 02:04:00.767
Seven-ninety-two. 795!

2029
02:04:00.851 --> 02:04:02.894
Drive it down. A.J.!

2030
02:04:02.978 --> 02:04:06.023
Seven-ninety-seven! 99!

2031
02:04:06.106 --> 02:04:09.401
- Breakthrough!
- Eight hundred! 802. Harry!

2032
02:04:09.860 --> 02:04:11.320
- Yeah!
- We did it!

2033
02:04:11.403 --> 02:04:13.363
Harry. we did it!

2034
02:04:13.447 --> 02:04:15.073
- Yes!
- We did it!

2035
02:04:15.157 --> 02:04:19.119
- Yeah! Kid. way to go!
- I knew it. baby!

2036
02:04:19.286 --> 02:04:21.330
It's not over
till we get the bomb down that hole.

2037
02:04:21.413 --> 02:04:23.707
Watts. they've got 38 minutes.

2038
02:04:44.019 --> 02:04:45.520
Harry. you've gotta give me that hole.

2039
02:04:45.604 --> 02:04:48.690
I'm gonna need two more minutes.
I got a bent pipe jammed in the hole.

2040
02:04:48.774 --> 02:04:51.818
We gotta cut it out before we can send
that bomb down. A.J.!

2041
02:04:52.486 --> 02:04:54.613
- She good to go?
- Yeah. I'm all set.

2042
02:04:54.696 --> 02:04:56.031
All right.

2043
02:05:01.411 --> 02:05:03.538
- All right.
- A.J.. come on! Make it fast!

2044
02:05:03.622 --> 02:05:07.250
I'm going as fast as I can!
There's a lot of gas pressure!

2045
02:05:13.924 --> 02:05:16.218
- You feel that?
- Harry. you gotta give me that hole.

2046
02:05:16.301 --> 02:05:17.344
The bomb is almost ready.

2047
02:05:17.427 --> 02:05:19.930
- Pull that pipe out!
- Harry. I'm almost through!

2048
02:05:20.013 --> 02:05:21.056
Give me 15 more seconds!

2049
02:05:27.187 --> 02:05:29.314
Well. this is something new.

2050
02:05:31.775 --> 02:05:32.984
I don't think this thing likes us.

2051
02:05:33.068 --> 02:05:34.611
That's 'cause it knows we're here
to kill it.

2052
02:05:41.368 --> 02:05:43.620
Hey. what's going on up there?

2053
02:05:48.250 --> 02:05:51.837
- A.J.!
- What the hell was that?

2054
02:05:51.920 --> 02:05:54.965
- A.J.!
- Goddamn it. I'm finished!

2055
02:05:56.508 --> 02:05:59.469
- A.J.. you all right?
- Lot of gas pressure in here. man!

2056
02:05:59.553 --> 02:06:02.639
- Get me out!
- Whoa. whoa. whoa! Hydrogen pocket!

2057
02:06:20.365 --> 02:06:22.659
Harry! Pull me in!

2058
02:06:27.080 --> 02:06:28.582
A.J.. hang on!

2059
02:06:34.254 --> 02:06:35.839
Secure the bomb!

2060
02:06:37.132 --> 02:06:38.717
Sharp. heads up!

2061
02:06:39.801 --> 02:06:42.179
Gruber! Get out of there now!

2062
02:06:43.930 --> 02:06:45.140
Oh. no.

2063
02:06:53.106 --> 02:06:55.108
God. no!

2064
02:07:01.615 --> 02:07:03.074
Look out!

2065
02:07:06.203 --> 02:07:09.748
Help! Oh. no!

2066
02:07:16.755 --> 02:07:19.216
Do you believe that just happened?

2067
02:07:22.260 --> 02:07:24.471
- Sharp. you all right?
- I'm okay.

2068
02:07:24.554 --> 02:07:26.973
- Bear?
- Yeah. I'm here. Harry.

2069
02:07:27.057 --> 02:07:29.559
- A.J.?
- Yeah. I'm okay.

2070
02:07:32.103 --> 02:07:33.647
We lost Gruber.

2071
02:07:35.398 --> 02:07:36.900
Gruber's dead.

2072
02:07:37.609 --> 02:07:39.486
Let's get that bomb ready
and go home.

2073
02:07:47.577 --> 02:07:48.620
Oh. my God.

2074
02:07:50.288 --> 02:07:52.165
Is there a problem. Colonel?

2075
02:07:52.249 --> 02:07:54.793
The timer. the remote.
the whole thing's dead.

2076
02:07:54.876 --> 02:07:56.878
What. the bomb is dead?

2077
02:07:56.962 --> 02:07:58.463
No. the trigger's dead.

2078
02:07:58.547 --> 02:08:01.633
It must've gotten damaged
during the rock storm.

2079
02:08:03.134 --> 02:08:05.136
So how do we detonate it?

2080
02:08:14.855 --> 02:08:19.693
We have 18 minutes to zero barrier.
We got some bad news.

2081
02:08:19.776 --> 02:08:23.738
The remote detonator on the bomb
has been damaged.

2082
02:08:23.822 --> 02:08:27.200
That means that somebody's
gonna have to stay behind.

2083
02:08:28.577 --> 02:08:31.162
It takes two people to fly this thing.

2084
02:08:31.246 --> 02:08:35.876
Either we all stay and die.
or you guys draw straws.

2085
02:08:35.959 --> 02:08:39.671
I say we all stay and die.
But that's me.

2086
02:08:40.755 --> 02:08:43.675
I'll draw. Let's draw.

2087
02:08:44.968 --> 02:08:48.013
Nobody's gonna draw straws.

2088
02:08:48.096 --> 02:08:51.057
- I'll stay and take care of it.
- Well. I can't live with that sort of thing.

2089
02:08:51.141 --> 02:08:52.767
Nobody asked you
if you could live with it. all right?

2090
02:08:52.851 --> 02:08:57.564
No way I will let you volunteer for this
so I can go back to my home country

2091
02:08:57.647 --> 02:08:59.399
like the man who didn't volunteer.

2092
02:08:59.482 --> 02:09:01.109
No way!

2093
02:09:01.192 --> 02:09:03.612
Hey. man. let's draw.

2094
02:09:03.737 --> 02:09:05.614
and let's see who's gonna stay up here
and dance.

2095
02:09:05.697 --> 02:09:08.533
Guys. I know you guys think
I'm crazy right now.

2096
02:09:08.617 --> 02:09:11.536
but I would really like
this responsibility.

2097
02:09:12.287 --> 02:09:14.080
All right. All right.

2098
02:09:15.206 --> 02:09:16.416
- I can do it.
- Let's just draw straws

2099
02:09:16.499 --> 02:09:19.252
- and get it over with. Come on.
- I ain't drawing against you. Harry.

2100
02:09:19.336 --> 02:09:20.754
Well. I'm gonna draw
against you. Chick.

2101
02:09:20.837 --> 02:09:23.965
so you better just go ahead and do it.

2102
02:09:24.049 --> 02:09:26.009
Just give me this thing.

2103
02:09:33.808 --> 02:09:35.727
Is this good or bad?

2104
02:09:41.566 --> 02:09:42.859
Oh. man.

2105
02:09:44.527 --> 02:09:47.489
Well. we all gotta die. right?

2106
02:09:50.784 --> 02:09:53.662
I'm the guy who gets to do it
saving the world.

2107
02:09:53.745 --> 02:09:57.040
So. let's go. We...
We got about 10 minutes. right?

2108
02:09:59.209 --> 02:10:01.378
You plug this into the port.

2109
02:10:01.461 --> 02:10:05.632
Lift. press. hold. That's it.

2110
02:10:05.715 --> 02:10:08.301
Lift. press. hold.
Shouldn't be too tough.

2111
02:10:08.385 --> 02:10:10.220
Even I can't screw this up.

2112
02:10:10.303 --> 02:10:12.055
I'll take him down.

2113
02:10:47.465 --> 02:10:50.677
Do me a favour. will you?
Just tell Grace that...

2114
02:10:52.595 --> 02:10:55.098
That I'll always be with her. okay?

2115
02:10:57.434 --> 02:10:59.019
Can you do that?

2116
02:11:00.979 --> 02:11:03.106
Yeah. Okay. kid.

2117
02:11:09.863 --> 02:11:11.698
Give this to Truman.

2118
02:11:11.781 --> 02:11:14.743
Make sure Truman gets that.
Get in there.

2119
02:11:20.915 --> 02:11:22.542
It's my turn now.

2120
02:11:23.877 --> 02:11:26.254
Harry! Harry!

2121
02:11:26.337 --> 02:11:28.298
You can't do this to me!

2122
02:11:29.632 --> 02:11:31.051
It's my job!

2123
02:11:31.843 --> 02:11:35.972
You go take care of my little girl now.
That's your job.

2124
02:11:39.392 --> 02:11:42.562
Always thought of you
as a son. Always.

2125
02:11:43.897 --> 02:11:46.900
But I'd be damn proud
to have you marry Grace.

2126
02:11:48.151 --> 02:11:51.404
- Harry.
- You take care of yourself.

2127
02:11:51.488 --> 02:11:52.947
- Harry. no!
- I love you. pal.

2128
02:11:53.031 --> 02:11:56.534
Harry. I love you!
Don't. Harry! Wait a minute!

2129
02:11:56.618 --> 02:11:58.578
- My son.
- No. don't do this. Harry!

2130
02:11:58.661 --> 02:12:01.414
You don't do this! Harry!

2131
02:12:09.839 --> 02:12:11.341
What happened?

2132
02:12:12.050 --> 02:12:14.427
That crazy. stubborn son of a...

2133
02:12:21.267 --> 02:12:23.561
Well. this was a real good idea.

2134
02:12:24.604 --> 02:12:28.316
All right. let's go. Sharp.
Let's get our team out of here.

2135
02:12:33.488 --> 02:12:36.449
Come on!
Let's get ready to initiate thrusters!

2136
02:12:36.533 --> 02:12:39.577
Strap it in. guys! Let's go!
Strap it in. guys!

2137
02:12:39.661 --> 02:12:40.870
Get the 02 masks.

2138
02:12:40.954 --> 02:12:43.456
- Are they free? Are they free?
- B.P.U.. set.

2139
02:12:43.540 --> 02:12:45.667
I cannot believe
this is going down like this.

2140
02:12:45.750 --> 02:12:47.127
You all right?

2141
02:12:47.210 --> 02:12:50.505
- 02 vents locked. pressure loaded.
- Engine board is green.

2142
02:12:53.216 --> 02:12:56.010
<i>T minus three minutes and counting.</i>

2143
02:12:56.094 --> 02:12:58.680
Houston. do you copy?
This is Harry Stamper.

2144
02:12:59.889 --> 02:13:01.474
It's down there.

2145
02:13:03.810 --> 02:13:08.606
<i>-Electrical systems primed.
- B.P.U. is set. Oxidizers are loading.</i>

2146
02:13:08.690 --> 02:13:13.027
<i>Houston. we're out of here
in T minus three minutes.</i>

2147
02:13:13.111 --> 02:13:14.279
Daddy?

2148
02:13:15.321 --> 02:13:18.074
Hi. Gracie. Hi. honey.

2149
02:13:19.200 --> 02:13:22.287
<i>Grace. I know I promised you
I was coming home.</i>

2150
02:13:23.538 --> 02:13:25.456
I don't understand.

2151
02:13:26.958 --> 02:13:30.086
<i>Looks like I'm gonna have
to break that promise.</i>

2152
02:13:32.589 --> 02:13:36.551
I... I lied to you. too.

2153
02:13:36.634 --> 02:13:39.846
when I told you
that I didn't want to be like you.

2154
02:13:41.431 --> 02:13:43.308
Because I am like you.

2155
02:13:44.184 --> 02:13:48.605
And everything good that I have
inside of me. I have from you.

2156
02:13:49.814 --> 02:13:51.858
<i>I love you so much. Daddy.</i>

2157
02:13:52.442 --> 02:13:54.235
I'm so proud of you.

2158
02:13:54.986 --> 02:13:56.487
<i>I'm so scared.</i>

2159
02:13:57.113 --> 02:13:58.615
<i>I'm so scared.</i>

2160
02:13:59.908 --> 02:14:02.368
I know it. baby.

2161
02:14:02.452 --> 02:14:05.622
but there won't be anything
to be scared of soon.

2162
02:14:06.998 --> 02:14:11.920
<i>Gracie. I want you to know
that A.J. saved us. He did.</i>

2163
02:14:14.464 --> 02:14:16.341
<i>I want you to tell Chick</i>

2164
02:14:16.424 --> 02:14:19.802
<i>that I couldn't have done it without him.
none of it.</i>

2165
02:14:21.804 --> 02:14:24.140
<i>I want you to take care of A.J.</i>

2166
02:14:28.645 --> 02:14:31.898
I wish I could be there
to walk you down the aisle.

2167
02:14:34.901 --> 02:14:36.319
But I'll...

2168
02:14:38.947 --> 02:14:42.200
I'll look in on you from time to time.
okay. honey?

2169
02:14:44.869 --> 02:14:46.329
I love you. Grace.

2170
02:14:46.829 --> 02:14:48.164
I love you. too.

2171
02:14:48.456 --> 02:14:50.875
- I gotta go now. honey.
- Daddy. no.

2172
02:14:52.210 --> 02:14:54.796
No. no. Dad. no!

2173
02:15:01.678 --> 02:15:05.014
O.M.S. pod pre-start.
02 vents locked. pressure loaded.

2174
02:15:07.100 --> 02:15:09.727
What the hell's going on up there?
Why haven't you guys left yet?

2175
02:15:09.811 --> 02:15:12.146
We're going. Harry. Houston.

2176
02:15:12.230 --> 02:15:14.899
- We got O.M.S. pod pre-start.
- Pod pre-start confirmed.

2177
02:15:18.611 --> 02:15:19.654
- What's the problem?
- I don't know.

2178
02:15:19.737 --> 02:15:21.823
- What's wrong?
- Fix it now!

2179
02:15:23.283 --> 02:15:25.285
We got no time. no time!

2180
02:15:25.368 --> 02:15:27.078
- What?
- What's that?

2181
02:15:31.124 --> 02:15:32.500
- Where you going?
- Come on.

2182
02:15:32.583 --> 02:15:34.294
We're staying. we're going.
We're staying. we're going.

2183
02:15:34.377 --> 02:15:35.378
Make up your minds.

2184
02:15:35.461 --> 02:15:38.339
Damn it. Sharp! Get out of here now.
You got less than three minutes.

2185
02:15:42.719 --> 02:15:46.055
- Come on. Watts. Come on. come on.
- Blow the bomb. Harry. We're with you.

2186
02:15:46.723 --> 02:15:48.224
- It's stuck. Yes?
- Come on!

2187
02:15:48.308 --> 02:15:50.059
Back off!
You don't know the components!

2188
02:15:50.143 --> 02:15:53.813
Components. American components.
Russian components.

2189
02:15:53.896 --> 02:15:55.356
All made in Taiwan!

2190
02:15:55.732 --> 02:15:57.859
We're getting tight
for ignition. <i>Freedom.</i>

2191
02:16:01.070 --> 02:16:03.156
- Houston. we've got no fire.
- What does that mean?

2192
02:16:03.239 --> 02:16:04.532
It means we got a busted ship.

2193
02:16:04.615 --> 02:16:07.160
A busted ship?
And I'm strapped in here?

2194
02:16:07.243 --> 02:16:09.287
I had a great spot picked out there.

2195
02:16:09.579 --> 02:16:10.663
<i>Freedom.</i> you fire that engine.

2196
02:16:10.747 --> 02:16:12.874
If there's not a way. you find a way.
The clock's ticking.

2197
02:16:12.957 --> 02:16:14.751
<i>Let's go!
Let's fire that engine.</i> Freedom!

2198
02:16:15.501 --> 02:16:19.464
You got less than a minute.
Don't think I won't blow this thing.

2199
02:16:20.631 --> 02:16:23.176
Sharp. get out of here.
It's getting bad down here.

2200
02:16:23.259 --> 02:16:25.345
I know how to fix it. Please. move.

2201
02:16:25.428 --> 02:16:27.764
I... I have to take you away
if you don't move.

2202
02:16:27.847 --> 02:16:29.432
Watts. you gotta get
that shuttle started.

2203
02:16:29.515 --> 02:16:30.767
You gotta fire it up now!

2204
02:16:30.933 --> 02:16:32.894
Damn it. Sharp. Get off this rock!

2205
02:16:32.977 --> 02:16:35.021
I'm telling you. please. move!

2206
02:16:35.104 --> 02:16:40.360
This is how we fix problem
in Russian space station.

2207
02:16:40.443 --> 02:16:43.654
Because I don't want
to stay here any more.

2208
02:16:45.281 --> 02:16:49.202
Yeah! Finally! We can go home!

2209
02:16:49.285 --> 02:16:50.495
She's coming back.
She's coming back.

2210
02:16:50.661 --> 02:16:51.704
We're hot!

2211
02:16:51.788 --> 02:16:53.122
Watts. let's go. let's go!

2212
02:16:54.791 --> 02:16:57.418
Rain all you want. you son of a bitch.

2213
02:16:58.294 --> 02:17:01.255
Let's go! We don't have time!
Hurry. hurry. We got no time!

2214
02:17:01.339 --> 02:17:05.134
Initiate thrusters on my mark!
Two. one. mark!

2215
02:17:13.309 --> 02:17:14.936
Come on. Get some altitude.
Let's go. let's go.

2216
02:17:15.019 --> 02:17:16.479
Yes! Come on!

2217
02:17:18.481 --> 02:17:19.565
<i>Freedom</i> has max thrust!

2218
02:17:27.365 --> 02:17:28.574
Thank you. Harry.

2219
02:17:40.169 --> 02:17:42.004
Shuttle's out of range.
Still no detonation.

2220
02:17:46.717 --> 02:17:48.678
Something's not right.
Too much time has gone by.

2221
02:17:51.389 --> 02:17:53.599
Zero barrier's about to be breached.
One minute.

2222
02:17:53.683 --> 02:17:55.309
Harry. come on. Press that button.

2223
02:17:56.519 --> 02:18:00.690
- We're going back and do it ourselves.
- Just don't. Wait one minute.

2224
02:18:04.944 --> 02:18:06.529
Dan. we're about to cross the threshold.

2225
02:18:06.612 --> 02:18:07.864
Come on. Harry. Press the button.

2226
02:18:07.989 --> 02:18:12.869
Colonel. I'm asking you.
Just one more minute!

2227
02:18:19.542 --> 02:18:20.877
Press the button. Stamper.

2228
02:18:24.589 --> 02:18:25.840
Come on.

2229
02:18:28.676 --> 02:18:30.803
Harry will do it. I know it.

2230
02:18:32.305 --> 02:18:33.639
He doesn't know how to fail.

2231
02:18:41.731 --> 02:18:43.316
We win. Gracie!

2232
02:18:44.108 --> 02:18:45.151
Press it!

2233
02:19:18.851 --> 02:19:21.646
<i>We have detonation.
Confirming detonation.</i>

2234
02:19:39.580 --> 02:19:41.874
<i>The two halves are gonna miss us
by 400 miles</i>

2235
02:19:41.958 --> 02:19:45.253
<i>and most of the small particles
have been vaporized.</i>

2236
02:19:56.305 --> 02:19:59.058
- Houston. we're coming home.
- <i>We copy that.</i> Freedom.

2237
02:19:59.141 --> 02:20:02.144
Yo. Harry. You the man.

2238
02:20:55.698 --> 02:20:59.577
Kennedy. we see you.
And you never looked so good.

2239
02:20:59.660 --> 02:21:03.122
I never told anybody this before.
but I hate flying.

2240
02:21:03.205 --> 02:21:05.541
so it'd be an awful shame to die now.

2241
02:21:05.625 --> 02:21:07.043
That's easy for you to say.

2242
02:21:07.126 --> 02:21:09.629
I owe 100 grand
to a bad-ass loan shark

2243
02:21:09.712 --> 02:21:12.381
which I spent on a stripper
named Molly Mounds.

2244
02:21:12.465 --> 02:21:15.676
- Boy. that's bad.
- Kennedy. we are 100%.

2245
02:21:15.760 --> 02:21:18.095
Flap suspension control on full.

2246
02:21:30.816 --> 02:21:32.818
Welcome home. astronauts.

2247
02:21:41.243 --> 02:21:43.329
Hey. guys. remember.
We're... We're heroes now.

2248
02:21:43.412 --> 02:21:45.831
So that incident with me
and the gun on the asteroid.

2249
02:21:45.915 --> 02:21:48.376
let's keep that under wraps. all right?

2250
02:22:52.690 --> 02:22:54.150
Miss Stamper?

2251
02:22:56.068 --> 02:22:59.405
Colonel Willie Sharp.
United States Air Force. ma'am.

2252
02:22:59.488 --> 02:23:02.408
Requesting permission
to shake the hand of the daughter

2253
02:23:02.491 --> 02:23:04.869
of the bravest man I've ever met.

2254
02:23:11.459 --> 02:23:12.918
Hello.

2255
02:23:13.002 --> 02:23:15.755
- Oh. my God!
- Hi! You're my hero!

2256
02:23:15.838 --> 02:23:19.675
Baby.
I wanna have babies with you.

2257
02:23:21.677 --> 02:23:23.512
Welcome back. cowboy.

2258
02:23:26.182 --> 02:23:28.976
Harry wanted you to have this.

2259
02:23:35.900 --> 02:23:37.318
He did. huh?

2260
02:23:56.128 --> 02:23:57.713
<i>I could stay awake</i>

2261
02:23:57.797 --> 02:24:02.968
<i>Just to hear you breathing</i>

2262
02:24:03.052 --> 02:24:06.972
<i>Watch you smile
while you are sleeping</i>

2263
02:24:07.056 --> 02:24:11.519
<i>While you're faraway and dreaming</i>

2264
02:24:11.602 --> 02:24:15.189
<i>I just wanna stay with you</i>

2265
02:24:15.272 --> 02:24:18.317
<i>In this moment forever</i>

2266
02:24:18.400 --> 02:24:21.320
<i>Forever and ever</i>

2267
02:24:21.403 --> 02:24:25.324
<i>I don't wanna close my eyes</i>

2268
02:24:25.407 --> 02:24:27.868
<i>I don't wanna fall asleep</i>

2269
02:24:27.952 --> 02:24:29.995
<i>'Cause I'd miss you. baby</i>

2270
02:24:30.079 --> 02:24:33.207
<i>And I don't wanna miss a thing</i>

2271
02:24:33.290 --> 02:24:37.211
<i>'Cause even when I dream of you</i>

2272
02:24:37.294 --> 02:24:39.755
<i>The sweetest dream would never do</i>

2273
02:24:39.839 --> 02:24:41.882
<i>I'd still miss you. baby</i>

2274
02:24:41.966 --> 02:24:45.177
<i>And I don't wanna miss a thing</i>

2275
02:24:45.261 --> 02:24:49.181
<i>And I don't wanna miss one smile</i>

2276
02:24:49.265 --> 02:24:53.143
<i>And I don't wanna miss one kiss</i>

2277
02:24:53.227 --> 02:24:56.730
<i>Well. I just wanna be
with you right here</i>

2278
02:24:56.814 --> 02:25:00.943
<i>With you just like this</i>

2279
02:25:01.026 --> 02:25:05.072
<i>Well. I just wanna hold you close</i>

2280
02:25:05.155 --> 02:25:09.451
<i>Feel your heart so close to mine</i>

2281
02:25:09.535 --> 02:25:13.122
<i>And just stay here in this moment</i>

2282
02:25:13.205 --> 02:25:17.877
<i>For all the rest of time</i>

2283
02:25:18.168 --> 02:25:20.087
<i>Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah</i>

2284
02:25:20.170 --> 02:25:23.132
<i>Yeah</i>

2285
02:25:23.215 --> 02:25:26.844
<i>Don't wanna close my eyes</i>

2286
02:25:26.969 --> 02:25:29.388
<i>I don't wanna fall asleep</i>

2287
02:25:29.471 --> 02:25:31.557
<i>'Cause I'd miss you. baby</i>

2288
02:25:31.640 --> 02:25:34.727
<i>And I don't wanna miss a thing</i>

2289
02:25:34.810 --> 02:25:38.689
<i>'Cause even when I dream of you</i>

2290
02:25:38.772 --> 02:25:41.317
<i>The sweetest dream would never do</i>

2291
02:25:41.400 --> 02:25:43.402
<i>I'd still miss you. baby</i>

2292
02:25:43.485 --> 02:25:46.822
<i>And I don't wanna miss a thing</i>

2293
